<HEAD>CB Radio Rescues Family Swamped By High Waves On Beach</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AYR, Scotland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A family trapped in a van on a beach by a
rising tide was rescued Sunday after calling for help on a citizens
band radio, police said.
   A ham radio operator forwarded the message to the Ayr coast
guard, which arrived at a waterfront esplanade near Ayr to find
waves breaking over the van occupied by Colin and Iris Rutherford
and their 4-month-old son, Colin.
   They were treated for shock and exposure at Ayr Hospital and
released, said a Glasgow police spokesman who demanded anonymity.
Ayr is 50 miles south of Glasgow on Scotland's west coast.
   The family, from Ayr, had been driving along the shore when
their vehicle stalled in the rising tidewaters, the spokesman said.
