<DOCNO> AP881009-0021 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-10-09-88 1121EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Honasan-Baby     10-09 0152</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Honasan-Baby,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Honasan's Wife Has Baby</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The wife of former Lt. Col. Gregorio
Honasan, the leader of the coup attempt that nearly toppled the
government last year, has given birth to a girl, it was reported
Sunday.
   Manila newspapers said Klarissa Honasan was born Friday to Jane
Honasan and weighed 7 pounds, 6 ounces. The baby is the couple's
fifth child.
   Honasan led the Aug. 28, 1987 coup attempt against President
Corazon Aquino's government in which at least 53 people died and
hundreds were wounded.
   Honasan was arrested in December but escaped in April and
remains at large.
   Mrs. Honasan told the Philippine Daily Inquirer that she has
received many visitors at the hospital in suburban Mandaluyong
since Klarissa's birth. But her husband, one of the country's most
wanted fugitives, has not been among them. ``Oh, but there'll be
time later,'' Mrs. Honasan was quoted as saying.
</TEXT>
