<HEAD>Kansas Traffic Accident Kills Six</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Mlle in 3rd graf is cq.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>PRESCOTT, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The fiery head-on collision of a car and a
pick-up killed six people, five members of one family, and injured
a seventh person, authorities said Sunday.
   The pick-up's gasoline tank ruptured and both vehicles burst
into flames, said investigators from the Kansas Highway Patrol. The
acccident happened at 10 p.m. Saturday on U.S. 69 in eastern Kansas.
   The only survivor in either vehicle was Mlle Brocaw, 18, of
Mound City, whose parents and three young brothers died at the
scene. She was reported in stable condition Sunday at Baptist
Memorial Hospital in Kansas City, Mo.
   Investigators said they had not determined which vehicle was
traveling in the wrong direction.
