<HEAD>Train Derails At Full Speed, 20 Feared Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The last two cars of a passenger
train traveling at full speed derailed Sunday night in a station in
eastern Yugoslavia, and 20 people were feared dead, the state news
agency Tanjug said.
   At least 15 others were seriously injured in the accident, which
occurred at 7:20 p.m. in Lapovo station, 49 miles south of
Belgrade, the news agency said.
   The train was en route from the southern city of Skopje to
Belgrade when the cars derailed and rammed into the engine of a
freight train parked in the Lapovo terminal, Tanjug said.
   Belgrade radio described the impact as ``tremendous.''
   Special rescue teams were trying to extricate passengers from
the tangled mass of metal, the reports said without giving a cause
of the accident.
   Other details were not immediately available.
