<HEAD>3 People Missing in Maine Surf; Searches Halted</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YORK, Maine (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rescuers called off their search Sunday for
three people missing and believed drowned in the Atlantic Ocean,
including a father and daughter swept into heavy surf as two other
family members watched.
   ``You can't give up hope, but the most we can probably hope for
is is to try to find (the bodies) for their families,'' said police
Sgt. Gary Finley.
   Terry Hundley, 41, of Durham, N.H., and his 11-year-old daughter
Marisol were swept into the ocean, with his wife and son watching,
after the family walked to the rocky shore near Bald Head Cliff to
watch 15-foot waves break Sunday morning, Finley said.
   A young boy was lost in the sea about a mile away in Ogunquit,
authorities said. Officials did not know the child's identity,
Coast Guard Petty Officer 1st Class Gary Salamacha said.
   Air and sea searches were futile, Coast Guard officials and
police said. Searches will resume Monday morning, Finley said.
